    },
    "Hebrew diacritization model by Elazar Gershuni · MIT License" : {
      "comment" : "Nakdimon library description",
      "localizations" : {
        "he" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "מודל ניקוד עברי מאת אלעזר גרשוני · רישיון MIT"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Hebrew is a right-to-left language, but many programs don’t support RTL text. When you paste Hebrew into these apps, the characters appear in reverse order — rendered left-to-right instead of right-to-left. The Reverse tool flips the character order so the text displays correctly in LTR-only software." : {

    },
    "Hebrew is written and read from right to left. The alphabet has been in continuous use for over 3,000 years, making it one of the oldest writing systems still in active use today." : {

    },
    "Hebrew Keyboard Layout" : {

    },
    "Hebrew text transformation utility for macOS. Convert keyboard layouts, strip niqqud, transliterate between modern and paleo-Hebrew scripts, and more." : {
      "comment" : "App description in About",
      "localizations" : {
        "he" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "כלי עזר להמרת טקסט עברי עבור macOS. המרת פריסות מקלדת, הסרת ניקוד, תעתוק בין כתב עברי מודרני וקדום, ועוד."
          }
        }
      }
