    "Ktav Ashuri is the script required for Torah scrolls, mezuzot, and tefillin. Jewish law (halakha) specifies that these sacred texts must be written in this script by a trained scribe (sofer). The Talmud (Sanhedrin 21b–22a) records a debate about whether the Torah was originally given in Ktav Ashuri or Paleo-Hebrew, reflecting the historical transition between the two scripts." : {

